nchanged while adding a new file. I’m considering whether to modify build.gradle, but I want to avoid new dependencies. There’s a possibility that without adjusting build.gradle, native compile will fail in this environment. The tests must run under a native image, which complicates things. I’ll ensure the path for the jar entry is set correctly using PomPropertiesUtil. I'll create the properties file and ensure the JarArchiver correctly adds it to the archive in the proper sequence.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering configuration settings**\\\\n\\\\nI might need to set `setForced(true)` as the default. I also need to use `java.util.Properties.load(InputStream)` to properly load properties from a jar entry. This seems straightforward, but I just want to make sure everything is in the right order and check that other configurations won't interfere with this approach. It’s crucial to keep things organized to avoid any unexpected issues later on. I’m focusing on getting this right!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating features effectively**\\\\n\\\\nI think I need to focus on picking a different uncovered feature, specifically from PomPropertiesUtil rather than placeholders. It seems important to avoid duplicating tested features since existing placeholders don't cover them. I'm considering whether the changes should reflect upstream, which might be fine, but I definitely want to ensure that there's no direct reflection. That sounds good, and I need to document what I've written so far.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_JDi5jQj9FCeWtrSl5B7KTwnv|fc_088c43fe69dfbf67016a0375f80afc819ea2092d072d3f95f6\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-archiver/2.5/src/test/java/org_apache_maven/maven_archiver/PomPropertiesUtilTest.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_apache_maven.maven_archiver;\\n\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse;\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\\n\\nimport java.io.IOException;\\nimport java.io.InputStream;\\nimport java.io.Reader;\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\\nimport java.util.Properties;\\nimport java.util.jar.JarEntry;\\nimport java.util.jar.JarFile;\\n\\nimport org.apache.maven.archiver.PomPropertiesUtil;\\nimport org.apache.maven.model.Model;\\nimport org.apache.maven.project.MavenProject;\\nimport org.codehaus.plexus.archiver.jar.JarArchiver;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class PomPropertiesUtilTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void createPomPropertiesWritesProjectCoordinatesAndAddsThemToArchive() throws Exception {\\n        Path testDirectory = testDirectory(\\\"archive-pom-properties\\\");\\n        Path pomPropertiesFile = testDirectory.resolve(\\\"generated/pom.properties\\\");\\n        Path archiveFile = testDirectory.resolve(\\\"application.jar\\\");\\n        MavenProject project = newProject(\\\"com.acme\\\", \\\"service\\\", \\\"1.0.0\\\");\\n        JarArchiver archiver = new JarArchiver();\\n        archiver.setDestFile(archiveFile.toFile());\\n\\n        new PomPropertiesUtil().createPomProperties(project, archiver, pomPropertiesFile.toFile(), false);\\n        archiver.createArchive();\\n\\n        assertCoordinates(loadProperties(pomPropertiesFile), \\\"com.acme\\\", \\\"service\\\", \\\"1.0.0\\\");\\n        try (JarFile jarFile = new JarFile(archiveFile.toFile())) {\\n            JarEntry entry = jarFile.getJarEntry(\\\"META-INF/maven/com.acme/service/pom.properties\\\");\\n            assertNotNull(entry);\\n            try (InputStream inputStream = jarFile.getInputStream(entry)) {\\n                assertCoordinates(loadProperties(inputStream), \\\"com.acme\\\", \\\"service\\\", \\\"1.0.0\\\");\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void createPomPropertiesKeepsMatchingExistingFileWhenNotForced() throws Exception {\\n        Path testDirectory = testDirectory(\\\"preserve-existing-pom-properties\\\");\\n        Path pomPropertiesFile = testDirectory.resolve(\\\"pom.properties\\\");\\n        Files.writeString(pomPropertiesFile, \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n                # preserved by the test\\n                artifactId=service\\n                groupId=com.acme\\n                version=1.0.0\\n                \\\"\\\"\\\", StandardCharsets.ISO_8859_1);\\n\\n        new PomPropertiesUtil().createPomProperties(\\n                newProject(\\\"com.acme\\\", \\\"service\\\", \\\"1.0.0\\\"), new JarArchiver(), pomPropertiesFile.toFile(), false);\\n\\n        String content = Files.readString(pomPropertiesFile, StandardCharsets.ISO_8859_1);\\n        assertTrue(content.contains(\\\"# preserved by the test\\\"));\\n        assertFalse(content.contains(\\\"Generated by Maven\\\"));\\n        assertCoordinates(loadProperties(pomPropertiesFile), \\\"com.acme\\\", \\\"service\\\", \\\"1.0.0\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void createPomPropertiesRewritesExistingFileWhenForced() throws Exception {\\n        Path testDirectory = testDirectory(\\\"force-pom-properties\\\");\\n        Path pomPropertiesFile = testDirectory.resolve(\\\"pom.properties\\\");\\n        Files.writeString(pomPropertiesFile, \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n                # preserved by the test\\n                artifactId=service\\n                groupId=com.acme\\n                version=1.0.0\\n                \\\"\\\"\\\", StandardCharsets.ISO_8859_1);\\n\\n        new PomPropertiesUtil().createPomProperties(\\n                newProject(\\\"com.acme\\\", \\\"service\\\", \\\"1.0.0\\\"), new Ja